This species can be distinguished from other species of its genus by the dark blue frons and body of adults, the terminal segment of penis in profile gradu- ally widened distally and with its lateral lobes triangular and median process very slender, the wing tips hyaline, and the basal spot on hind wings small and extending at most to half way between first and second antenodals (
